k the catch could hide any native failures, especially without assertions if it hits an UnsupportedFeature. \\\\n\\\\nI want to keep it for class loading tests but remove it for resource lookup since the target class is known to the class loaders. I should also clean up by removing unused imports like InvokerHelper while retaining NativeImageSupport. Let's proceed with those edits!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_c2h4u1PtOT1uRoPjtFJMG35C|fc_0a6e7474391d17770169f5a7639b1081948a30ba2818d6a5cf\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoaderTest.groovy\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.InvokerHelper\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\\n\", \"newText\": \"import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    void compiledAccessorScriptExercisesGeneratedHelperMethods() {\\n        try {\\n            GroovyClassLoader groovyClassLoader = new GroovyClassLoader(getClass().classLoader)\\n            Class<?> scriptClass = groovyClassLoader.parseClass('''\\n                package groovy.inspect.swingui\\n\\n                @groovy.transform.CompileStatic\\n                class GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoaderAccessor extends Script {\\n                    Object run() {\\n                        GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader loader = new GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader(new groovy.lang.GroovyClassLoader())\\n                        String missingResourceName = 'org/codehaus/groovy/groovy-all/generated-bytecode-aware-loader-test-resource.txt'\\n\\n                        Class<?> classFromHelper = GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader.class$(GeneratedBytecodeAwareGroovyClassLoader.name)\\n                        Class<?> missingLoadedClass = loader.super$2$findLoadedClass('org.codehaus.groovy.groovy_all.NotLoade